        Checks if the move is valid.

      • isBoardFull

        public boolean isBoardFull()
        Checks if the board is full.
        Returns:
        returns true if board is full. Returns false if board has atleast one Mark.EMPTY spot.

      • horizontalWin

        public boolean horizontalWin(Mark m,
                    int index)
        Determines if the move with the given Mark will lead to a horizontal win.
        Parameters:
        m - the Mark of the move.
        index - the place where the Mark is placed
        Returns:
        returns true when there is a horizontal four in a row. Returns false when there is no four in a row.

      • scanDiagonalLeftUp

        public int scanDiagonalLeftUp(Mark m,
                     int index)
        Scan the indices left up of the Mark placement. Returns a value representing the connecting Marks in the direction.
        Parameters:
        m - the Mark of the move.
        index - the place where the Mark is placed
        Returns:
        return an integer between 0 and 3. Based on the amount of equal Marks beneath index. Return 3 means four Marks are connected.
